    "Rodolfo Villela Marino and his brother Ricardo, each own a nearly 4% stake in Brazil's Itau Unibanco.",
    "His grandfather Eudoro Libânio Villela cofounded Itau in 1945 in Sao Paulo.",
    "In 2008, Itau merged with Unibanco to create the largest private sector bank (by assets) in Latin America.",
    "Villela Marino sits on the board of Itausa, the parent of Itau Unibanco, and has served as executive vice president since 2022.",
    "In 2015, his mother, Maria de Lourdes Egydio Villela, a former billionaire, transferred her stake in the bank to Villela and his brother Ricardo."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Villela has a degree in business and a doctorate in management from the Getúlio Vargas Foundation (FGV) in São Paulo."
